&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Strike&#39;s mission is to build a more connected financial world.&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strike allows users to send and receive money anywhere, instantly, with no fees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strike is built on top of the Bitcoin network - the largest global, interoperable and open payments standard. Strike believes that open payment networks enable universal participation in the financial system, ushering in a new digital economy with truly borderless money transfers. Strike leverages Bitcoin’s open payment network to offer users the first global peer-to-peer payments app and a novel bitcoin-native neobanking experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Role:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strike is looking to hire a Customer Support Team Lead with experience in handling suspicious accounts in a fintech setting. Come join our rapidly expanding support team as we bring Bitcoin payments to the world. The successful candidate will answer related support tickets, act as an escalation point and collaborate with the backend team to enhance fraud prevention infrastructure. The role involves developing support processes for ticket handling, and briefing the team of all new procedures and latest fraud trends. The successful candidate will be in charge of overseeing the management of this critical support topic. The ideal candidate should thrive working in a fast paced, startup environment and be excited about Strike’s mission and potential. The person joining us must be comfortable with a team-first approach in a remote work environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
